title: Ceiling Paper, 1905–15
inscribed: Printed in selvedge: "Gossler & Wilt W. P. Co. Phila 726"
description:
Flower-like shapes made up of one floral wreath over four foliate wreaths and tendrils. Fleurons in the resulting negative spaces. Ground is light green blue. Printed in light blue, white mica, and gold micas. 
Printed in selvedge: "Gossler & Wilt W. P. Co. Phila 726"

participants.person_name: Gossler and Wilt Wall Paper Co.

tombstone.epitaph:
Ceiling Paper, 1905–15.
1905–15. Machine-printed on paper, mica, liquid. Gift of Victorian Collectibles. 1979-91-1157.
